	url = {https://www.scopus.com/pages/publications/105034848524?origin=resultslist},
	affiliations = {Nmims, Navi Mumbai, India},
	abstract = {Motor vehicle insurance compliance verification is crucial for ensuring regulatory adherence and protecting policyholders' interests in the rapidly growing Indian insurance market. Traditional compliance methods face significant challenges including time-consuming manual reviews, human error due to oversight, and difficulty in scaling operations to handle thousands of policy documents. This research presents a hybrid AI framework combining Legal-BERT for domain-specific understanding, Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) with ChromaDB for regulation retrieval, and LLaMA 3.3 for intelligent reasoning to automate compliance verification. The system achieves 92% classification accuracy while processing documents in 5-15 seconds, operating in a zero-shot manner without policy-level annotations. This framework demonstrates the viability of hybrid RAG-LLM architectures for complex legal document analysis, providing insurance companies with a scalable, accurate, and explainable compliance verification solution that significantly reduces manual effort and improves regulatory consistency. © 2025 IEEE.},
