	affiliations = {University of Tsukuba, Japan; Yayoi Co., Ltd., Japan},
	abstract = {In this paper, we introduce the Yayoi QA v1.1 dataset, a comprehensive resource tailored for question answering in accounting domain, and evaluate responses generated within a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) framework. The dataset is derived from systematically curated tutorial pages published by Yayoi Co., Ltd., a leading accounting software company in Japan, covering a breadth of content from fundamental knowledge about accounting laws and procedures to detailed instructions on using accounting applications. It is designed to answer a wide range of questions posed by non-expert users performing accounting tasks. Employing an embedding-based search mechanism, we retrieve the top five documents most similar to each query, and then propose multiple methods for using large language models (LLMs) to generate contextually accurate answers grounded in the retrieved information. We conduct evaluation experiments with various LLMs for each proposed method. Human assessments of our experimental results indicate that the proposed methods achieve a high accuracy rate of 90.00% when handling specialized accounting questions. © 2025 IEEE.},
