	year = {2025},
	journal = {Conference Proceedings - 2025 IEEE Silchar Subsection Conference, IEEE SILCON 2025},
	pages = {},
	doi = {10.1109/SILCON67893.2025.11326921},
	url = {https://www.scopus.com/pages/publications/105034964133?origin=resultslist},
	affiliations = {Dr. N.G.P Arts and Science College, Department of Computer Science With Data Analytics, Coimbatore, India},
	abstract = {Companies create and store data in a variety of formats such as PDF documents, Excel workbooks and SQL databases. These different formats store data in different ways and as the volume of files increases, locating the right data manually becomes a very time-consuming, challenging task. Frequently employees need to manually check each file and get the insight. To overcome this problem, the multimodal agentic AI framework has been introduced where each agent is dedicated to be data specialized in a specific type. The PDF Agent converts not only the text-based documents but also the scanned ones with the help of OCR. The Excel Agent identifies sheets, tables, formulas, charts, pivot tables, and slicers. The SQL Agent extracts data from relational databases. This kind of structure enables people to ask their questions in normal human language and the system gets to work with finding the right answers and provides them automatically from the existing data. It is the use of RAG together with the LLM model such as Gemini 2.0 Flash language model that makes the framework deliver accurate answers coming from enterprise-specific data and it also lessens the probability of errors and irrelevant outputs that standalone LLMs may produce. Such a methodology has the potential to be a great internal tool for enterprises to manage huge amount of data. A sample app was built as a proof of concept for this framework. People can interrogate varied data in their own language and get the right answers. It is useful in many areas such as research, education and businesses where people want to get information from documents without checking each one.  © 2025 IEEE.},
	author_keywords = {Agentic AI Framework; Enterprise Data Management; Multimodal Agent; Natural Language Querying; Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)},
