	abstract = {Artificial Intelligence (AI) has been increasingly explored in various industries, and the application of the Retrieval- Augmented Generation (RAG) technique emerges as a promising solution for creating AI assistants that optimize complex processes, such as regulatory compliance in the pharmaceutical industry. The RAG technique combines information retrieval with text generation. This approach becomes especially relevant in a sector that faces growing challenges in interpreting and adhering to a large volume of frequently updated regulations. Regulatory compliance in the pharmaceutical industry demands not only information management but also precision and efficiency in interpreting standards, something that can be compromised by manual processes susceptible to errors. These challenges pose risks of non- compliance, legal sanctions, and damage to companies' reputations. The creation of the AI assistant using the RAG technique provides a significant advantage by allowing employees to obtain information quickly and accurately, without the need for manual analysis of databases. © 2026 by IGI Global Scientific Publishing. All rights reserved.},
